solution.p:
On the second interval [0,\sqrt{5}], the height of increments is given by h(x) = x - (x^3-4x) = 5x-x^3 because now the cubic polynomial is the bottom curve. The corresponding area is A_2 = \int_{0}^{\sqrt{5}} 5x- x^3 \, dx which has a value
A_2 &= \int_{0}^{\sqrt{5}} 5x- x^3 \, dx &= 5\int_{0}^{\sqrt{5}} x \, dx - \int_{0}^{\sqrt{5}} x^3 \, dx &= 5\left( \frac{1}{2}(\sqrt{5})^2\right) - \left(\frac{1}{4}(\sqrt{5})^4\right) &= \frac{25}{2} -\frac{25}{4} &= \frac{25}{4}
As we should expect from symmetry, the two areas are equal A_1=A_2.
